cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about improving the generalization of a coreference resolution system, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses adversarial training, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves retraining a state-of-the-art system, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions named entities, which are often used in natural language processing tasks, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category. Finally, the paper uses the GAP dataset, which involves gendered pronoun resolution, a task that can be related to computer vision, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible category.
